events.description: The Augustinian monastic order is constituted at the Lecceto Monastery when Pope Alexander IV issues a papal bull Licet ecclesiae catholicae.

events.description: Religious reformer John Wycliffe is condemned as a heretic at the Council of Constance.
events.html: • 1415 – Religious reformer John Wycliffe is condemned as a heretic at the Council of Constance.[2]

events.description: Assassination of the Swedish rebel (later national hero) Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson (27 April O.S.).
events.html: • 1436 – Assassination of the Swedish rebel (later national hero) Engelbrekt Engelbrektsson (27 April O.S.).[3]

events.description: Wars of the Roses: The Battle of Tewkesbury: Edward IV defeats a Lancastrian Army and kills Edward of Westminster, Prince of Wales.

entities.name: Edward of Westminster, Prince of Wales

events.description: In the papal bull Inter caetera, Pope Alexander VI divides the New World between Spain and Portugal along the Line of Demarcation.
events.html: • 1493 – In the papal bull Inter caetera, Pope Alexander VI divides the New World between Spain and Portugal along the Line of Demarcation.[5]

events.description: Dutch explorer Peter Minuit arrives in New Netherland (present day Manhattan Island) aboard the See Meeuw.
events.html: • 1626 – Dutch explorer Peter Minuit arrives in New Netherland (present day Manhattan Island) aboard the See Meeuw.[6]

events.description: The Imperial Theatrical School, the first ballet school in Russia, is founded.
events.html: • 1738 – The Imperial Theatrical School, the first ballet school in Russia, is founded.[7]

events.description: Rhode Island becomes the first American colony to renounce allegiance to King George III.
events.html: • 1776 – Rhode Island becomes the first American colony to renounce allegiance to King George III.[8]

entities.name: Colony of Rhode Island and Providence Plantations

events.description: Fourth Anglo-Mysore War: The Battle of Seringapatam: The siege of Seringapatam ends when the city is invaded and Tipu Sultan killed by the besieging British army, under the command of General George Harris.
events.html: • 1799 – Fourth Anglo-Mysore War: The Battle of Seringapatam: The siege of Seringapatam ends when the city is invaded and Tipu Sultan killed by the besieging British army, under the command of General George Harris.[9]

events.description: Emperor Napoleon arrives at Portoferraio on the island of Elba to begin his exile.
events.html: • 1814 – Emperor Napoleon arrives at Portoferraio on the island of Elba to begin his exile.[10]

events.description: King Ferdinand VII abolishes the Spanish Constitution of 1812, returning Spain to absolutism.
events.html: • 1814 – King Ferdinand VII abolishes the Spanish Constitution of 1812, returning Spain to absolutism.[11]

events.description: Formation of Ancient Order of Hibernians.
events.html: • 1836 – Formation of Ancient Order of Hibernians.[12]

events.description: The Cornwall Railway opens across the Royal Albert Bridge linking Devon and Cornwall in England.
events.html: • 1859 – The Cornwall Railway opens across the Royal Albert Bridge linking Devon and Cornwall in England.[13]

events.description: The four-day Naval Battle of Hakodate begins. The newly formed Imperial Japanese Navy defeats the remnants of the Tokugawa shogunate navy in the Sea of Japan off the city of Hakodate, leading to the surrender of the Ezo Republic on May 17.
events.html: • 1869 – The four-day Naval Battle of Hakodate begins. The newly formed Imperial Japanese Navy defeats the remnants of the Tokugawa shogunate navy in the Sea of Japan off the city of Hakodate, leading to the surrender of the Ezo Republic on May 17.[14]

events.description: The National Association, the first professional baseball league, opens its first season in Fort Wayne, Indiana.
events.html: • 1871 – The National Association, the first professional baseball league, opens its first season in Fort Wayne, Indiana.[15]

entities.name: National Association of Professional Base Ball Players

events.description: Haymarket affair: In Chicago, United States, a homemade bomb is thrown at police officers trying to break up a labor rally, killing one officer. Ensuing gunfire leads to the deaths of a further seven officers and four civilians.
events.html: • 1886 – Haymarket affair: In Chicago, United States, a homemade bomb is thrown at police officers trying to break up a labor rally, killing one officer. Ensuing gunfire leads to the deaths of a further seven officers and four civilians.[16]

events.description: The United States begins construction of the Panama Canal.
events.html: • 1904 – The United States begins construction of the Panama Canal.

events.description: The Royal Canadian Navy is created.
events.html: • 1910 – The Royal Canadian Navy is created.[17]

events.description: Italy occupies the Ottoman island of Rhodes.
events.html: • 1912 – Italy occupies the Ottoman island of Rhodes.

events.description: May Fourth Movement: Student demonstrations take place in Tiananmen Square in Beijing, China, protesting the Treaty of Versailles, which transferred Chinese territory to Japan.
events.html: • 1919 – May Fourth Movement: Student demonstrations take place in Tiananmen Square in Beijing, China, protesting the Treaty of Versailles, which transferred Chinese territory to Japan.

events.description: The United Kingdom general strike begins.
events.html: • 1926 – The United Kingdom general strike begins.

events.description: The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences is incorporated.
events.html: • 1927 – The Academy of Motion Picture Arts and Sciences is incorporated.[18]

events.description: Having been incarcerated at the Cook County Jail since his sentencing on October 24, 1931, mobster Al Capone is transferred to the federal penitentiary in Atlanta after the U.S. Supreme Court denies his appeal for conviction of tax evasion.
events.html: • 1932 – Having been incarcerated at the Cook County Jail since his sentencing on October 24, 1931, mobster Al Capone is transferred to the federal penitentiary in Atlanta after the U.S. Supreme Court denies his appeal for conviction of tax evasion.[19]

events.description: World War II: The Battle of the Coral Sea begins with an attack by aircraft from the United States aircraft carrier USS Yorktown on Japanese naval forces at Tulagi Island in the Solomon Islands. The Japanese forces had invaded Tulagi the day before.
events.html: • 1942 – World War II: The Battle of the Coral Sea begins with an attack by aircraft from the United States aircraft carrier USS Yorktown on Japanese naval forces at Tulagi Island in the Solomon Islands. The Japanese forces had invaded Tulagi the day before.

events.description: World War II: Neuengamme concentration camp near Hamburg is liberated by the British Army.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: Neuengamme concentration camp near Hamburg is liberated by the British Army.

events.description: World War II: The German surrender at Lüneburg Heath is signed, coming into effect the following day. It encompasses all Wehrmacht units in the Netherlands, Denmark and northwest Germany.
events.html: • 1945 – World War II: The German surrender at Lüneburg Heath is signed, coming into effect the following day. It encompasses all Wehrmacht units in the Netherlands, Denmark and northwest Germany.

events.description: In San Francisco Bay, U.S. Marines from the nearby Treasure Island Naval Base stop a two-day riot at Alcatraz Federal Penitentiary.  Five people are killed in the riot.
events.html: • 1946 – In San Francisco Bay, U.S. Marines from the nearby Treasure Island Naval Base stop a two-day riot at Alcatraz Federal Penitentiary. Five people are killed in the riot.

events.description: The entire Torino football team (except for two players who did not take the trip: Sauro Tomà, due to an injury and Renato Gandolfi, because of coach request) is killed in a plane crash.
events.html: • 1949 – The entire Torino football team (except for two players who did not take the trip: Sauro Tomà, due to an injury and Renato Gandolfi, because of coach request) is killed in a plane crash.

events.description: American civil rights movement: The "Freedom Riders" begin a bus trip through the South.
events.html: • 1961 – American civil rights movement: The "Freedom Riders" begin a bus trip through the South.

events.description: Malcolm Ross and Victor Prather attain a new altitude record for manned balloon flight ascending in the Strato-Lab V open gondola to 113,740 feet (34.67 km).
events.html: • 1961 – Malcolm Ross and Victor Prather attain a new altitude record for manned balloon flight ascending in the Strato-Lab V open gondola to 113,740 feet (34.67 km).

events.description: Vietnam War: Kent State shootings: The Ohio National Guard, sent to Kent State University after disturbances in the city of Kent the weekend before, opens fire killing four unarmed students and wounding nine others. The students were protesting the Cambodian Campaign of the United States and South Vietnam.
events.html: • 1970 – Vietnam War: Kent State shootings: The Ohio National Guard, sent to Kent State University after disturbances in the city of Kent the weekend before, opens fire killing four unarmed students and wounding nine others. The students were protesting the Cambodian Campaign of the United States and South Vietnam.

events.description: The Don't Make A Wave Committee, a fledgling environmental organization founded in Canada in 1971, officially changes its name to "Greenpeace Foundation".
events.html: • 1972 – The Don't Make A Wave Committee, a fledgling environmental organization founded in Canada in 1971, officially changes its name to "Greenpeace Foundation".

events.description: The 108-story Sears Tower in Chicago is topped out at 1,451 feet (442 m) as the world's tallest building.
events.html: • 1973 – The 108-story Sears Tower in Chicago is topped out at 1,451 feet (442 m) as the world's tallest building.[20]

events.html: • 1988 – The PEPCON disaster rocks Henderson, Nevada, as tons of Space Shuttle fuel detonate during a fire.
